New Records: Keyonte George tied his career high
Key Match Events: Coby White scored 28 points in the second half, tying it twice late in the third quarter
Utah outscored Chicago 21-11 to pull away
Pre-Game Insights: The Jazz played a third straight game without leading scorer Lauri Markkanen (back spasms)
The Bulls played without injured leading scorer Zach LaVine
Post-Match Reflections: The Jazz won their first game of the season
The Bulls have lost two in a row to drop to 3-4
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz shot 53.9% from the floor and were 45.7% from 3-pointer range at 16 of 35
Ayo Dosunmu scored 25 points on 9-for 13 shooting
Nikola Vucevic had 23 points for Chicago
Others: The Jazz had a season high in points
